chunks.name: ReferenceType
chunks.text:
Component Name: ReferenceType
Required Fields: [$ref]
Properties:
  - $ref: type=string  # The $id value of the referenced data component

chunks.name: PrologueType
chunks.text:
Component Name: PrologueType
Description: A common prologue on each data component
Type: object
Required Fields: [$id, lastUpdateTimeStamp, updatedByAgencyReference]
Properties:
  - $id: type=string  # Globally unique identifier of the data component
  - AlternateValueReferences: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # References to alternate values data component. Alternate values for data elements in this data component.
  - externalInformationSourceReferences: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # References to External Sources Data Components that are links to external information sources not otherwise defined in the EIDO.
  - lastUpdateTimeStamp: type=string (format: date-time)  # Timestamp of the last time the data component was modified
  - mediaReferences: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # References to Media Data Components that link to external media.
  - updatedByAgencyReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Owning Agency Identifier. This includes private and public providers. Agencies are globally unique.
  - updatedByAgentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # A globally unique identifier of the agent or automaton that updated the data component last

chunks.name: AlternateValuesType
chunks.text:
Component Name: AlternateValuesType
Description: Subscribers may need to see conflicting values not chosen by an inter-agency IDX coalescing algorithm. For this purpose, a data component for an EIDO is defined which contains the differences. For each data component where a constituent sends a candidate value that the IDX does not use in the EIDO proper, the IDX includes the “Alternate Values” data component. That data component has conflicting values from the constituents.
Type: object
Required Fields: [Alternate, DataComponentReference, Element]
Properties:
  - Alternate: type=array (items type: object)  # Alternate value for the element.
  - DataComponentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to the data component this alternate value applies to.
  - Element: type=string  # Name of Element in the referenced component.

chunks.name: AgencyType
chunks.text:
Component Name: AgencyType
Description: A data type for an organization that owns or is otherwise related to an emergency incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [agencyRoleDescriptionRegistryText, agencyType]
Properties:
  - actingOnBehalfOfAgencyReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to an agency data component. If the agency is operating on behalf of another agency as it’s backup, this contains a reference to the other agency’s agency data component.
  - agencyCallLegState: type=array (items are references to 'CallLegStateType')  # Represents the agency call leg state when it is different from the global call state. It SHOULD be omitted if the state of the call leg is the same as the call or when the call is known to be connected to an agent. When the call is connected to an agent, the agent’s agency call leg state SHOULD be omitted and assumed to be the same as the agent call leg state.
  - agencyJcard: type=string  # The agency’s contact information.
  - agencyRoleDescriptionRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Shall only contains values present in the Agency Role registry
  - agencyType: type=array (items type: string)  # One or more members of a list of available provider and agency types. The agency types are taken from the IANA urn:emergency:service:responder registry and the subregistries defined for that registry. Values exclude the “urn:emergency:service:responder.” prefix. Example values: “police.federal.fbi”, “fire.forest”, “poison_control” including: Law Enforcement, Fire, EMS, Consolidated Dispatch, Ambulance Company, etc. Agency Types are defined in the IANA urn:emergency:service:responder registry.
  - incidentOwningAgencyIndicator: type=boolean  # True if an agency owns the emergency incident; false otherwise
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the agency.

chunks.name: AgentType
chunks.text:
Component Name: AgentType
Description: A data type for information about agents (e.g., call takers, dispatchers, supervisors, responding emergency resources, etc.) and automated systems acting as agents that are involved in an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [agencyReference, agentRoleRegistryText]
Properties:
  - agencyReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Linked element type is AgencyType
  - agentCallLegState: type=array (items are references to 'CallLegStateType')  # Represents the agent call leg state when it is different from the global call state. It SHOULD be omitted if the state of the call leg is the same as the call.
  - agentJcard: type=string  # The agent’s contact information.
  - agentRoleRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Shall only contains values present in the Agent Role registry
  - agentWorkstationPositionIdentification: type=string  # The workstation position ID within the agent’s agency.
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the agent.

chunks.name: IncidentMergeDirectionCodeSimpleType
chunks.text:
Component Name: IncidentMergeDirectionCodeSimpleType
Description: A data type for a code list for a direction of a merge or split.
Type: string
Allowed Values (Enum): [REPLACING, REPLACED, SPLIT]

chunks.name: MergeInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: MergeInformationType
Description: A data type for information about a merged or split incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [incidentMergeDirectionCode, incidentTrackingIdentifier]
Properties:
  - incidentMergeDirectionCode: (Reference to component 'IncidentMergeDirectionCodeSimpleType')
  - incidentTrackingIdentifier: type=string  # The Incident Tracking Identification of the Incident that is being merged with, or split from the Incident.

chunks.name: LinkDirectionCodeSimpleType
chunks.text:
Component Name: LinkDirectionCodeSimpleType
Description: A data type for a code list for a kind of link performed.
Type: string
Allowed Values (Enum): [PARENT, CHILD, RELATED, UNLINK]

chunks.name: LinkInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: LinkInformationType
Description: A data type for information about a linked incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [incidentTrackingIdentifier, linkDirectionCode]
Properties:
  - incidentTrackingIdentifier: type=string  # A globally unique emergency incident identifier.
  - involvedAgencyReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Agencies involved with the linked incident. Must be populated if the agency sending the EIDO is not involved with the linked incident.
  - linkDirectionCode: (Reference to component 'LinkDirectionCodeSimpleType')
  - transactionReasonText: type=string  # Free format narrative description of the reason for the link

chunks.name: NotesType
chunks.text:
Component Name: NotesType
Description: A data type for notes and comments associated with an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [notesActionComments]
Properties:
  - agentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Linked element type is AgentType
  - cautionReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to information used to raise special attention to circumstances related to this Note that might threaten the safety of people or property. Linked elements type are CautionType.
  - notesActionComments: type=string  # A note about an incident created by an agent; in HTML5 format.

chunks.name: AdditionalDataType
chunks.text:
Component Name: AdditionalDataType
Description: A data type for additional information associated with an incident call, location, or person.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Properties:
  - additionalDataByReferenceUrl: type=string  # A URL that references additional data associated with a call.
  - additionalDataByValue: type=string  # Additional data associated with a call.
  - additionalDataDereferencedFromReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to the Additional Data data component containing the source additionalDataByReferenceUrl when additionalDataByValue came from a dereference operation.
  - cautionReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A reference used to raise special attention to circumstances related to this Additional Data that might threaten the safety of people or property. Linked elements type are CautionType.
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Notes and comments associated with an incident. Linked elements type are NotesType
  - urlPurpose: type=string  # Purpose that accompanied the URL. For example, the purpose parameter sent with the URL in the Call-Info headers.

chunks.name: LocationInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: LocationInformationType
Description: A data type for a location associated with an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [locationTypeDescriptionRegistryText]
Properties:
  - additionalDataReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Additional information associated with an incident call, location, or person. Linked elements type are AdditionalDataType
  - cellTowerSectorId: type=string  # The nearest cell tower and sector/face of the tower receiving a call associated with an incident.
  - crossStreetByReferenceUrl: type=array (items type: string)  # A URL where a nearest cross street to an incident's location can be dereferenced.
  - crossStreetByValue: type=array (items type: string)  # A nearest cross street to an incident's location in PIDF-LO format.
  - intersectingStreetByReferenceUrl: type=array (items type: string)  # A URL where an additional street, that with the location forms an intersection, can be dereferenced.
  - intersectingStreetByValue: type=array (items type: string)  # An additional street, that with the location forms an intersection, in PIDF-LO format.
  - localIdentifier: type=array (items type: string)  # An identifier generated by the agency that shared the location that refers to this location in their local systems/databases.
  - locationByReferenceUrl: type=string (format: uri)  # A URL where a location associated with an incident can be dereferenced.
  - locationByValue: type=string  # A type for an external adapter for a Presence Information Data Format-Location Object (PIDF-LO).
  - locationDereferencedFromReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to the location data component containing the source locationByReferenceUrl when locationByValue came from a dereference operation.
  - locationDescriptionText: type=string  # Optional text further describing the location type.
  - locationTypeDescriptionRegistryText: type=string  # Shall only contains values present in the Location type registry
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Notes and comments associated with an incident. Linked elements type are NotesType

chunks.name: PersonInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: PersonInformationType
Description: A data type for information about a person associated with an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [personIncidentRoleRegistryText]
Properties:
  - additionalDataReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Additional information associated with an incident call, location, or person. Linked elements type are AdditionalDataType
  - callBackReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a call back data component. Identifies how the person described in this data component can be called back.
  - callIdentifier: type=array (items type: string)  # Call Identifier of the calls this person was involved on.
  - destinationReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Location Data Component specifying where the person is going. When the destination is a place to meet responders, the location type is set to 'Staging'.
  - eta: type=string (format: date-time)  # A timestamp of when the person is expected to reach the destination.
  - itemReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to an item that the person carries or has direct access to. Linked elements type is ItemInformationType.
  - locationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A location associated with an Person. Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - ncPersonComponent: (Reference to component 'ncPersonType')
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the person.
  - personCallLegState: type=array (items are references to 'CallLegStateType')  # A representation of the person call leg state when it is different from the global call state. SHOULD be omitted if the state of the call leg is the same as the call.
  - personIncidentRoleRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Shall only contains values present in the Person Role registry

chunks.name: OrganizationInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: OrganizationInformationType
Description: Information about organizations associated with an Incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [organizationIncidentRoleRegistryText]
Properties:
  - additionalDataReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Additional Data about an organization. Linked elements type are AdditionalDataType
  - callBackReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a call back data component. Identifies how the organization described in this data component can be called back.
  - locationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A location associated with an organisation. Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - ncOrganizationComponent: (Reference to component 'ncOrganizationType')
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the organization.
  - organizationIncidentRoleRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Contains values from the Organization Incident Role registry.

chunks.name: DispositionType
chunks.text:
Component Name: DispositionType
Description: A data type for incident disposition information entered or updated by a dispatch agent and/or a responding emergency resource.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [dispositionCommonRegistryCode]
Properties:
  - dispositionCategoryText: type=string
  - dispositionCommonRegistryCode: type=string  # Shall only contains values present in the Common Disposition Code registry
  - dispositionDescriptionText: type=string
  - dispositionPrimaryIndicator: type=boolean  # True if the common disposition is the primary disposition for an agency for an incident; false otherwise.
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the incident.

chunks.name: VehicleInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: VehicleInformationType
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [vehicleRelationshipTimeStamp, vehicleRelationshipType]
Properties:
  - additionalDataReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Additional information associated with a vehicle. Linked elements type is AdditionalDataType
  - destinationReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Location Data Component specifying where the vehicle is going. When the destination is a place to meet responders, the location type is set to 'Staging'.
  - eta: type=string (format: date-time)  # A timestamp of when the vehicle is expected to reach the destination.
  - itemReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to an item that is in or on the vehicle. Linked elements type is ItemInformationType
  - jCommercialVehicleComponent: (Reference to component 'jCommercialVehicleType')
  - locationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A location associated with an vehicle. Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - ncVehicleComponent: (Reference to component 'ncVehicleType')
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the vehicle.
  - vehicleRelationshipTimeStamp: type=string (format: date-time)  # The date and time that the relationship of the vehicle to the incident was established
  - vehicleRelationshipType: type=array (items type: string)  # Information about a vehicle associated with an incident. Shall only contains values present in the Vehicle Relationship Type registry

chunks.name: IncidentInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: IncidentInformationType
Description: A data type for general information about emergency incidents gathered by emergency agents, responding emergency resources, from reporting parties (callers), and devices reporting emergency incidents.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [incidentTypeCommonRegistryText]
Properties:
  - agentReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Linked elements type is AgentType
  - beatOrDispatchGroupText: type=string  # A beat or dispatch group that contains an incident.
  - dispositionComponent: type=array (items are references to 'DispositionType')  # Incident disposition information entered or updated by a dispatch agent and/or a responding emergency resource.
  - documentIdentification: type=array (items type: string)
  - incidentCommonPriorityNumber: type=integer (format: int32)  # A globally unique priority of an incident.
  - incidentPriorityInternalText: type=string  # An internal value used by a local agency for the priority of an incident.
  - incidentStatusCommonRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Shall only contains values present in the Incident Status registry
  - incidentStatusInternalText: type=array (items type: string)  # An internal code used by a local agency for a status of an incident.
  - incidentTypeCommonRegistryText: type=string  # Shall only contains values present in the Incident Type registry
  - incidentTypeInternalCode: type=string  # An alphanumeric code indicating the category of the incident. This is the internal code used by the local agencies involved in the incident.
  - incidentTypeInternalText: type=string  # Textual description indicating the category of the incident. This is the internal text used by the local agencies involved in the incident.
  - internalIncidentId: type=string
  - locationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A location associated with an incident. Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the incident.
  - organizationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about an organizations associated with an incident. Linked elements type is OrganizationInformationType
  - personReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about a person associated with an incident. Linked elements type is PersonInformationType
  - reportNumberType: type=string
  - vehicleReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about a vehicle associated with an incident. Linked elements type is VehicleInformationType

chunks.name: UpdatedCBNType
chunks.text:
Component Name: UpdatedCBNType
Description: A data type for additional telephone numbers and SIP equivalents that can be used to contact the individual that made a call associated with an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [updatedCbnIdentifierUri]
Properties:
  - updatedCbnCallerDescription: type=string  # Additional descriptive text about an updated caller call back number such as the days and hours to use it and the type of number (e.g., work, home, friend, etc.).
  - updatedCbnIdentifierUri: type=string (format: uri)  # A telephone number or SIP equivalent of a reporting party described in the parent call.

chunks.name: CallInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: CallInformationType
Description: A data type for call information about an incident received and collected by an agent.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [callStartTimestamp, callStateRegistryText, direction, standardPrimaryCallType]
Properties:
  - additionalDataReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Additional information associated with an incident call, location, or person. Linked elements type is AdditionalDataType
  - agencyReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to an Agency Data Component containing information about agencies connected to the call. Used to know which agencies are connected to the call when information about the connected agent within these agencies is not known.
  - agentReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Linked elements type is AgentType
  - answerDate: type=string (format: date-time)  # A date and time stamp on which the call was answered by an agent.
  - callBackReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a call back data component. Identifies how the caller described in this data component can be called back.
  - callStartTimestamp: type=string (format: date-time)  # Date and time stamp of when the call was received.
  - callStateRegistryText: type=string  # Current call status (when the EIDO was created) from the available call statuses in the “Call States” registry i.e., callBegin, callAnswered, callEnd, partyAdd , etc. Values limited to those in the IANA CallStates registry.
  - direction: type=string  # 'incoming' means received by the EIDO sender, 'outgoing' means sent by the EIDO sender and 'internal' means both caller and recipient are within the EIDO sender.
  - localCallType: type=string  # Locally defined call type.
  - locationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A location associated with an incident. Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the call. Linked elements type are NotesType
  - organizationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about an organization associated with a call. Linked elements type is OrganizationInformationType
  - personReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about a person associated with an incident. Linked elements type is PersonInformationType
  - priorityIdentifier: type=string  # Call Priority Identifier defined in STA-023. It is used to describe the priority of a call.
  - queueIdentifier: type=string  # An identifier of a queue where the call is currently on.
  - relatedCallIdentifier: type=array (items type: string)  # CallIdentifier of calls that are related to this call. Eg Callbacks
  - sipIdentity: type=string  # Content of the SIP identity header. Required if known.
  - standardPrimaryCallType: type=string  # Values limited to those in the LogEvent CallTypes registry with “Primary” classification.
  - standardSecondaryCallType: type=string  # Values limited to those in the LogEvent CallTypes registry with “Secondary” classification.
  - verstat: type=string  # Value of the verstat parameter. Required if known.

chunks.name: CallbackType
chunks.text:
Component Name: CallbackType
Description: This data component is used to exchange information about how to contact the Incident’s reporting parties.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Properties:
  - callBackInformationUri: type=array (items type: string)  # Information that enables agents and responders to call back. URI(s) found in the P-Asserted-Identity header if provided else the URI in the From header.
  - deviceContactHeader: type=string  # Content of the device contact header. Information that enables agents and responders to possibly reach (call back) the device that initiated the call.
  - updatedCbn: (Reference to component 'UpdatedCBNType')  # Identifies additional telephone numbers and SIP equivalents that can be used to contact.

chunks.name: EmergencyResourceType
chunks.text:
Component Name: EmergencyResourceType
Description: A data type for a resource (vehicle, person [foot patrol], organizational unit such as a squad or strike team, and other emergency responder configurations) that responds to an emergency incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [agentReference, emergencyResourceTypeCommonRegistryText, primaryUnitStatusRegistryText, resourceAttributeRegistryText, secondaryUnitStatusRegistryText]
Properties:
  - activeOnIncidentId: type=string  # Incident the resource is currently active on. If the unit is not active on any incident this data element will not be present. Version 1 EIDOs exclude this data element so it MUST be assumed the resource is active on the incident being represented in the version 1 EIDOs.
  - agentReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about agents (e.g., call takers, dispatchers, supervisors, responding emergency resources, etc.) and automated systems acting as agents that are involved in an incident. Linked elements type is AgentType
  - emergencyResourceName: type=string  # Common name of the emergency resource.
  - emergencyResourceTypeCommonRegistryText: type=string  # Shall only contains values present in the Emergency Resource Type registry
  - emergencyResourceTypeInternalText: type=string  # A local code for an emergency resource type.
  - eta: type=string (format: date-time)  # Timestamp of when the unit is expected to reach it's destination
  - itemReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to an item data component containing item information entered or updated directly by an emergency responder. Represent the item(s) used by the Emergency Resource. e.g., Weapons, tools, etc.. Linked elements type is ItemInformationType
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to a Notes Data Component. Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the incident.
  - personReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about a person associated with an incident. Linked elements type is PersonInformationType
  - primaryUnitStatusRegistryText: type=string  # Shall only contains values present in the Primary Unit Status registry
  - resourceAttributeInternalText: type=array (items type: string)  # A local code for an emergency resource attribute. Must be populated if the resourceAttributeRegistryText is set to 'Other'
  - resourceAttributeRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Shall only contains values present in the Resource Attribute registry
  - secondaryUnitStatusRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # Shall only contains values present in the Secondary Unit Status registry
  - stackedOnIncidentId: type=array (items type: string)  # Incident the resource is queued on. The order these incident ID is out of scope of this document.
  - unitDestinationReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - unitLocationReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - unitStatusInternal: type=array (items type: string)  # A local code for a status of an emergency resource.
  - vehicleReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Information about a vehicle associated with an incident. Linked elements type is VehicleInformationType

chunks.name: DispatchInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: DispatchInformationType
Description: A data type for dispatch information related to an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Properties:
  - agencyReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Reference to an AgencyType. Agency that was dispatched through action performed in this data component.
  - agentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Linked elements type is AgentType. Identifies the agent that completed the dispatch operation described
  - emergencyResourceReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A resource (vehicle, person [foot patrol], organizational unit such as a squad or strike team, and other emergency responder configurations) that responds to an emergency incident. Linked elements type is EmergencyResourceType
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the dispatch. Linked elements type are NotesType

chunks.name: AlarmsSensorsType
chunks.text:
Component Name: AlarmsSensorsType
Description: A data type for alarms and sensors information associated with an incident.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Properties:
  - agentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # Linked elements type is AgentType
  - alarmUrl: type=string (format: uri)  # A URL that references Central Station Alarm Association (CSAA) data associated with an incident.
  - csaaAlarmInformation: type=string  # Central Station Alarm Association (CSAA) data associated with an incident.
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the dispatch. Linked elements type are NotesType

chunks.name: MediaType
chunks.text:
Component Name: MediaType
Description: A data type representing a URI link to static or streaming media.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [contentType, uri]
Properties:
  - contentType: type=string  # An entry from the IANA “Media Types” registry
  - label: type=string  # A UTF8 label used to describe the media in a human readable format.
  - uri: type=string (format: uri-reference)  # A URI which when dereferenced will retrieve the media.

chunks.name: CallLegStateType
chunks.text:
Component Name: CallLegStateType
Description: A data type representing the agent call leg’s state when it is different from the global call state.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [callReference, callStateRegistryText]
Properties:
  - callReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to a Call Data Component that represents the call to which the call leg is related to.
  - callStateRegistryText: type=string  # An entry from the IANA “Call Status” registry

chunks.name: SharedCommunicationResourceType
chunks.text:
Component Name: SharedCommunicationResourceType
Description: A data type representing information about shared resources used for shared communication between agents and agencies for this Incident. This would include information about radio channels, talk groups, chat room, etc..
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [sharedCommunicationResourceType]
Properties:
  - connectedSharedCommunicationResources: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # References to Shared Communication Resource Data Components. It represents the other communication resources that share a communication path with this one. The referenced components should be part of the EIDO and reference this instance creating a circular reference. Implementations MUST take this fact into consideration to avoid circular reference exceptions.
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the related shared communication resource. Linked elements type are NotesType
  - sharedCommunicationResourceByReferenceUrl: type=string  # A URL referencing a link to a Shared Communication detail Data Component. This allows the dereferencing of Shared Communication Resource detail associated with an Incident.
  - sharedCommunicationResourceByValue: type=string  # A string representing the Shared Communication Resource detail Data Component provided by value.
  - sharedCommunicationResourceType: type=string  # Type of shared communication resource whose values limited to those in the SharedCommunicationResourceType registry.

chunks.name: ExternalInformationSourceType
chunks.text:
Component Name: ExternalInformationSourceType
Description: A data type representing external information sources not otherwise defined in the EIDO. The referenced external information source is likely to apply its own data right management policies while responding to any agencies trying to access the external data. This is not a replacement for Additional Data but can be used to provide a reference to an IS-ADR. A data provider SHOULD use the mechanism described in rfc7852 for any new sources of data about a call, person, or location.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [externalSourceRegistryText]
Properties:
  - externalSourceAcessString: type=string  # A string value that can be used to query the data source. For example, a URL or a query string, etc.
  - externalSourceRegistryText: type=string  # An Identifier that SHOULD come from the external information source registry. The registry values are linked to a description in the registry that gives details about how to access the data.

chunks.name: UnitEmergencyStateType
chunks.text:
Component Name: UnitEmergencyStateType
Description: A data type representing an emergency state reported for a unit. For example, an emergency button being pressed on a radio, or a vehicle reporting a severe crash.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [severity, startTimestamp]
Properties:
  - acknowledgementTimestamp: type=string (format: date-time)  # A date and time indicating the moment an agency acknowledges the emergency alarm.
  - emergencyStateType: type=string  # A type of emergency state. Types are listed in the emergency state registry.
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # Contains optional alphanumeric text further describing the component. Linked elements type are NotesType.
  - originatingDevice: type=string  # A user friendly alias for the device used to request/enter Unit Emergency State. An example could be a specific radio device such as Radio1334.
  - reportingAgentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to an Agent data component representing the agent who triggered initiation of the Unit Emergency State from the originating device. This agent might also be referenced by instances of Emergency Resource Data Component indicating the unit/resource the agent is a member of.
  - severity: type=string  # A value indicating the degree to which the state should be taken seriously that is estimated by the sending agent or agency.
  - startTimestamp: type=string (format: date-time)  # A date and time denoting the beginning of the Emergency State.
  - stopTimestamp: type=string (format: date-time)  # A date and time denoting the end of the Emergency State.
  - terminatingAgentReference: (Reference to component 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to an Agent data component representing the agent who terminated the Unit Emergency State.

chunks.name: CautionType
chunks.text:
Component Name: CautionType
Description: A data type used to raise special attention to circumstances related to a Person, Location or Vehicle that might threaten the safety of people or property.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [cautionSeverity, cautionTypeCommonRegistryText, cautionTypeInternalText]
Properties:
  - cautionSeverity: type=string  # A value indicating the degree to which the caution should be taken seriously that is estimated by the sending agent or agency.
  - cautionSource: type=string  # A person or agency that provided the caution information. If the information is provided by an agent with a known Agent Id, then the Agent Id must be the value. If the information is provided by an agency with a known Agency Id, then the Agency Id must be the value. If the information is provided by a person referenced in the EIDO then the person data component Identifier ($id) must be the value. Otherwise, the value is free form text describing the source.
  - cautionTypeCommonRegistryText: type=string  # A registry value further describing the caution. More than one is allowed when they are related.
  - cautionTypeCommonSubRegistryText: type=array (items type: string)  # A type of caution as described in the 'CautionType' registry.
  - cautionTypeInternalText: type=string  # A textual description indicating the type of caution information. This is the internal text used by the local agencies involved in the Incident.
  - startDate: type=string (format: date-time)  # A date and time a caution was first registered.

chunks.name: ItemInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: ItemInformationType
Description: A data type used to represent items that are of interest in the context of the incident. An Item can be something like a firearm (including of a specific type) or other weapon, medical equipement, jewelry, a credit card, sports equipment, musical instruments, etc. The list of valid Item types is very broad and is adopted from the NIEM ItemType.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Properties:
  - locationReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A location associated with an Person. Linked elements type is LocationInformationType
  - ncItemType: (Reference to component 'ncItemType')  # A data type for an article or thing. Many NIEM types extend the ItemType and can be represented in this field e.g. j:FirearmType,j:ExplosiveType, j:ContrabandType, j:JewelryType, etc...
  - notesReference: type=array (items are references to 'ReferenceType')  # A reference to optional information further describing the item. Linked elements type is NoteType.

chunks.name: EmergencyIncidentDataObjectType
chunks.text:
Component Name: EmergencyIncidentDataObjectType
Description: A data type for an information exchange containing emergency incident related data.
Inherits from: PrologueType
Required Fields: [agencyComponent, eidoVersion, issuingElementIdentification]
Properties:
  - @context: type=object  # JSON-LD context
  - additionalDataComponent: type=array (items are references to 'AdditionalDataType')  # All additional data referenced in this document are listed here.
  - agencyComponent: type=array (items are references to 'AgencyType')  # All agencies referenced in this document are listed here.
  - agentComponent: type=array (items are references to 'AgentType')  # All agents referenced in this document are listed here.
  - alarmsSensorsComponent: type=array (items are references to 'AlarmsSensorsType')  # Alarms and sensors information associated with an incident.
  - callComponent: type=array (items are references to 'CallInformationType')  # Call information about an incident received and collected by an agent.
  - callbackComponent: type=array (items are references to 'CallbackType')  # Contains information about how to call a person.
  - cautionComponent: type=array (items are references to 'CautionType')  # All caution information referenced in this document are listed here.
  - dispatchComponent: type=array (items are references to 'DispatchInformationType')  # Dispatch information related to an incident.
  - eidoExtensionId: type=array (items type: string)  # EIDO extension IDs identifying extension that are used in the EIDO instance. Values are to be included in the EIDO EidoExtensionId registry.
  - eidoVersion: type=string  # Version of the EIDO structure.
  - emergencyResourceComponent: type=array (items are references to 'EmergencyResourceType')  # All emergency resources information referenced in this document are listed here.
  - externalInformationSourceComponent: type=array (items are references to 'ExternalInformationSourceType')  # All external information sources not otherwise defined in the EIDO.
  - incidentComponent: (Reference to component 'IncidentInformationType')  # General information about the emergency incident gathered by emergency agents, responding emergency resources, from reporting parties (callers), and devices reporting emergency incidents.
  - issuingElementIdentification: type=string  # An identifier of a functional element that created the EIDO instance.
  - linkComponent: type=array (items are references to 'LinkInformationType')  # Information about a linked incident.
  - locationComponent: type=array (items are references to 'LocationInformationType')  # All location informations referenced in this document are listed here.
  - mediaComponent: type=array (items are references to 'MediaType')  # All media component information referenced in this document are listed here.
  - mergeComponent: type=array (items are references to 'MergeInformationType')  # Information about a merged or split incident.
  - notesComponent: type=array (items are references to 'NotesType')  # All notes referenced in this document are listed here.
  - personComponent: type=array (items are references to 'PersonInformationType')  # All person informations referenced in this document are listed here.
  - sharedCommunicationResourceComponent: type=array (items are references to 'SharedCommunicationResourceType')  # All shared resources used for shared communication between agents and agencies for this Incident.
  - vehicleComponent: type=array (items are references to 'VehicleInformationType')  # All vehicle informations referenced in this document are listed here.

chunks.name: EIDO Summary
chunks.text: Overall EIDO Summary: The Emergency Incident Data Object (EIDO) is a standardized, industry-neutral JSON format for exchanging the **current state** of an emergency incident. It facilitates interoperability between different systems (e.g., CAD, logging, call handling) across public safety agencies. A key feature of EIDO is its deep integration with the **National Information Exchange Model (NIEM)**. While EIDO defines the overall incident structure, it relies on NIEM to provide rich, standardized definitions for complex data entities like persons, vehicles, and organizations. This ensures the data is highly detailed and interoperable with a wide range of justice and public safety systems.

chunks.name: NIEM Integration Purpose
chunks.text: Purpose of NIEM Integration: EIDO does not redefine complex data types that are already well-established. Instead, it embeds objects defined by NIEM. This allows EIDO to carry extremely rich data for entities like people and vehicles, ensuring it is compatible with the broader national justice and public safety information sharing ecosystem.

chunks.name: NIEM Integration: Mechanism
chunks.text: Mechanism for NIEM Integration: 1. **NIEM Component Fields:** You will see fields ending in `...Component`, such as `ncPersonComponent` or `jCommercialVehicleComponent`. These fields contain complex objects whose structure is not defined by EIDO itself, but by the corresponding NIEM schemas (e.g., `nc.yaml`, `j.yaml`).       2. **JSON-LD Contexts:** EIDO uses a `@context` field that points to JSON-LD (Linked Data) files. This is the technical mechanism that maps the simple JSON property names in the EIDO file to their formal, globally-understood NIEM definitions. It's what allows a receiving system to understand that `nc:PersonBirthDate` in the NIEM model is represented by a specific field in the JSON object.

chunks.name: NIEM Integration: Implication for Agent
chunks.text: Implication for Agent for NIEM Integration: When you encounter a field like `ncPersonComponent`, you are not just getting a simple name and phone number. You are receiving a comprehensive, standardized data structure that can include everything from physical descriptions (scars, tattoos), multiple addresses, identification documents, and relationships, all defined by the NIEM standard. This provides a much deeper level of detail for your report than EIDO's core fields alone.

chunks.name: Component Context: EmergencyIncidentDataObjectType
chunks.text:
Component Name: EmergencyIncidentDataObjectType
Description: The root object of the EIDO. It is the main container for all incident-related information. The `$id` of this component is the globally unique Incident Tracking Identifier.
Key Fields:
  - eidoVersion: The version of the EIDO standard, which is "1.0".
  - issuingElementIdentification: Identifier of the functional element (system) that created this EIDO instance.
  - incidentComponent: The core details of the incident itself.
  - agencyComponent: A list of all agencies involved or referenced.
  - personComponent: A list of all persons (callers, victims, suspects) involved or referenced.
  - vehicleComponent: A list of all vehicles involved or referenced.
  - itemComponent: A list of all items of interest (weapons, equipment, etc.) referenced.

chunks.name: Component Context: PersonInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: PersonInformationType
Description: Information about a person associated with the incident. An instance should be created for every person, including callers, victims, suspects, and patients.
Key Fields:
  - personIncidentRoleRegistryText: The person's role in the incident, from the "EIDO-PersonRole" registry (e.g., 'Caller', 'Victim', 'Suspect').
  - ncPersonComponent: Richly detailed person information conforming to the NIEM standard. This can include physical descriptions, multiple names/aliases, identification documents, biometrics, etc.
  - locationReference: Reference to locations associated with this person.

chunks.name: Component Context: VehicleInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: VehicleInformationType
Description: Information about a vehicle associated with an incident.
Key Fields:
  - vehicleRelationshipType: The vehicle's role in the incident from the "EIDO-VehicleRelationshipType" registry (e.g., 'SuspectVehicle', 'AccidentVehicle').
  - ncVehicleComponent: Detailed vehicle information conforming to the NIEM standard. Includes make, model, year, color, VIN, and license plate.
  - jCommercialVehicleComponent: Additional detailed information specific to commercial vehicles, as defined by the NIEM Justice domain.

chunks.name: Component Context: OrganizationInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: OrganizationInformationType
Description: Information about organizations associated with an Incident (e.g., a company, a hospital).
Key Fields:
  - organizationIncidentRoleRegistryText: The organization's role in the incident from the 'Organization Incident Role' registry.
  - ncOrganizationComponent: Detailed organization information conforming to the NIEM standard, including names, locations, contact info, and identifiers.

chunks.name: Component Context: ItemInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: ItemInformationType
Description: Information about an item of interest, such as a firearm, medical equipment, or other property relevant to the incident.
Key Fields:
  - ncItemType: A detailed description of an article or thing, conforming to the NIEM standard. This is a generic base type that can be extended to represent specific items like firearms (`j:FirearmType`) or explosives.
  - locationReference: Reference to locations where the item is or was.

chunks.name: Component Context: IncidentInformationType
chunks.text:
Component Name: IncidentInformationType
Description: General information about an emergency incident, including its type, status, and priority.
Key Fields:
  - incidentTypeCommonRegistryText: A standardized incident type from the "EIDO-IncidentType-Common" registry (e.g., 'MVAINJY', 'BURGLARY').
  - incidentStatusCommonRegistryText: The current status of the incident from the "EIDO-IncidentStatus-Common" registry (e.g., 'Active', 'ResourcesOnscene').

chunks.name: Component Context: EmergencyResourceType
chunks.text:
Component Name: EmergencyResourceType
Description: A responding resource, such as a patrol car, fire engine, or ambulance. The `$id` is the unique unit ID.
Key Fields:
  - emergencyResourceTypeCommonRegistryText: The type of resource from the "EIDO-EmergencyResourceType-Common" registry (e.g., 'PatrolUnit', 'FireTruckLadder').
  - primaryUnitStatusRegistryText: The primary availability status from the "EIDO-PrimaryUnitStatus-Common" registry ('Available', 'ConditionallyAvailable', 'NotAvailable').
  - secondaryUnitStatusRegistryText: Detailed activity status from the "EIDO-SecondaryUnitStatus-Common" registry (e.g., 'Dispatched', 'EnRoute', 'OnScene').
